list_page_teaser: The image of each of the Sixteen Types has its own unique characteristics that mirror each of the 16 archetypal personalities.  Learn how the Groja program uses primary colors to construct the image of each of these types.
description_html:
This gallery contains a 'generic' image of each of the Sixteen Types. They are in alphabetical order by four-letter-type, and the preference ratio used in all images is 58% to 42%.

Using a fixed percentage rather than a real personality can make the images look similar, in that all of them are quite colorful. If you look closely, however, and read the stories and explanations, you can learn how each one definitively expresses the imaginary personality's preferences.
story_html:
In this context, calling these images 'generic' means they portray ficticious personalities whose preferences are set to a fixed percentage. For example, the score used to generate the image of an ISTP in this gallery is I:58%/E:42%, S:58%/N:42%, T:58%/F:42%, and P:58%/J:42%.

It is extremely important to note that people in real life rarely look like this!

And although we should all be proud of who we are, I strongly believe that we should never think for a second that one type is 'better' than another!

image_list.title: ENFJ - Generic
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an ENFJ using fixed percentages.
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: Images of ENFJs, like the images of the other xNFx types, contain more Red and Blue, and less Green and Yellow.  Click on the image to see a full-sized version, and to learn more about ENFJs and their images.
image_list.explain_dom: The long vertical Red lines in this image represent the ENFJ's Dominant personality trait, their Extraverted Feeling.  Their warmth causes them to seek harmonious relationships and enables them to make strong social connections.  This Extraverted Feeling makes ENFJs outgoing, polite, friendly, charming, and loyal.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter horizontal Blue lines represent the ENFJ's Auxiliary personality trait, their Introverted iNtuition.  Their openness to new ideas gives them the ability to reconcile seemingly contradictory evidence and gain sudden insight - an 'Aha!' moment - into future possibilities.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an ENFJ is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of ENFJ personality types.
